BANAYANA Banyana vice captain Refiloe Jane became the first South African Women player to score a goal in Italian football. In September 2019, the Banyana midfielder became the first South African to sign with Italian giants AC Milan when she penned a one-year deal. On Monday Jane helped her side to come back from 2-0 down and defeat Roma 3-2. The Banyana star scored a stunning goal to get an equaliser for her side before Berglind Björg Þorvaldsdóttir scored the winner in the 89th minute. .  